I could reproduce the problem (when the blocks directory is a symlink) on Ubuntu 20.04.3 LTS
I tried the patch below and it fixed the mentioned error  but another error still occurs when creating  `blocks/index`.

`filesystem error: cannot create directories: File exists [/home/.../.bitcoin/signet/blocks/index]`

```diff

// src/util/system.cpp
path /= fs::PathFromString(BaseParams().DataDir());
path /= "blocks";
-if (!fs::exists(path)) {
+if (!fs::exists(path) && !fs::is_symlink(path)) {
        fs::create_directories(path);
}

// src/init.cpp
-if (!fs::is_directory(gArgs.GetBlocksDirPath())) {
+if (!fs::is_directory(gArgs.GetBlocksDirPath()) && !fs::is_symlink(gArgs.GetBlocksDirPath())) {
        return InitError(strprintf(_("Specified blocks directory \"%s\" does not exist."), args.GetArg("-blocksdir", "")));
    }
```
